Step 2: Coverage-Driven Test Design (JUnit 5)
------------------------------------------------------------

Strategy:
Transitioned the test cases into an automated JUnit 5 suite, 
categorizing inputs by their logical execution paths to 
trigger every conditional branch in the target algorithm.

Branch Mapping:
- testBoundaryConditions: Eliminates the "Null Reference" 
  smell by ensuring defensive guard clauses (if present in 
  the Solution class) safely handle empty or null lists.
- testAlreadyAllEvens: Verifies the edge case where the first 
  list requires exactly zero exchanges (0 odds <= N evens).
- testSufficientEvens (YES Branch): Verifies paths where the 
  swap is fully possible, including exact matches (3 odds 
  and 3 evens) and surplus matches.
- testInsufficientEvens (NO Branch): Verifies the failure 
  path where the second list cannot satisfy the odd-replacement 
  requirements of the first list.

